<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-30T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-30T16:00:00-05:00" n="40" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/8543b: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-30T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            30, 1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>9465. Please inform the Supreme Council that in cases where
                                decisions, resolutions, or actions are taken by that body which do
                                not particularly interest the United States and are agreed to
                                without <pb facs="0134" n="32" xml:id="pg_32"/> your specific
                                approval, they should be so worded as to clearly indicate that they
                                represent the views of only those powers which have agreed to them.
                                In connection with this it is suggested that it should be made clear
                                that the expression “Principal Allied and Associated Powers” should
                                only be used when you have agreed to its use in any particular
                                instance.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>